body:
## Welcome to the Sea Star Web site
 

### Linked Data Crawl 2014
We experimented with the [Linked Data Crawl](http://data.dws.informatik.uni-mannheim.de/lodcloud/2014/ISWC-RDB/#toc0) generated in 2014 by Schmachtenberg et al. ([ISWC 2014  publication](http://dws.informatik.uni-mannheim.de/fileadmin/lehrstuehle/ki/pub/SchmachtenbergBizerPaulheim-AdoptionOfLinkedDataBestPractices.pdf)).

### Contexts in N-Quads

### Quality of N-Quads

### Predicates
By looking at the set of different predicates in the links, we classified them depending on their purpose. We identified quadruples that:
(Data set level)
* provide metadata about a data set or a vocabulary
(Schema level)
* define a vocabulary term (property or class)
* map vocabulary terms
(Entity level)
* classify an entity
* connect two identical entities
* connect two similar entities
* connect two related two entities, either with a domain-specific relationship (e.\,g.\texttt{foaf:knows}), or a more general relationship (e.\,g.\ \texttt{rdfs:seeAlso})
